er and athleticism. Variations of the snatch are often used in Strength and Conditioning programs for this reason. If you are just getting started with the Snatch then scroll to the bottom to download my <a href="https://www.strengthcoachglasgow.co.uk/snatch-handbook.html">free Snatch progressions handbook</a>.<br />&nbsp;<br /><u>Exercise Suitability:<br /></u>Beginners: &#10060;<br />Advanced: &#10004;&#65039;<br />&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br /><u>What are the key technique points?<br /></u><ul><li>Ensure you have a good understanding of the full movement (perhaps built up using my progressions) before training to perform this</li><li>Maintain your back angle until the bar passes your knees while pushing your feet through the floor to generate power with your legs.</li><li>As the bar reaches the hip (power position) think about jumping or exploding vertically upwards while trying to keep the bar moving in as straight a line as possible<br /></li><li>Secure the bar overhead by punching your hands up into the bar as your feet secure to the platform.</li></ul></div>  <div class="wsite-youtube" style="margin-bottom:10px;margin-top:10px;"><div class="wsite-youtube-wrapper wsite-youtube-size-auto wsite-youtube-align-center"> <div class="wsite-youtube-container">  <iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/MrihPJ4vJew?wmode=opaque" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> </div> </div></div>  <div class="paragraph">&#8203;<span style="color:rgb(42, 42, 42)">If you'd like to have everything taken care of for you then I offer both in-person&nbsp;<a href="https://www.strengthcoachglasgow.co.uk/personal-training.html">1-2-1 personal training in Glasgow</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.strengthcoachglasgow.co.uk/online-training.html">online personal training</a>. You can check them out by clicking each option or&nbsp;<a href="https://www.strengthcoachglasgow.co.uk/contact.html">send me a message now</a>&nbsp;if you have any questions.</span><br /><br /><span style="color:rgb(42, 4